# LDCPortfolio Sources Base Rule

Use this map to quickly locate the correct place for changes.

## Key Directories

- `src/main.tsx`: application entry point and React root render.
- `src/App.tsx`: top-level composition (providers, loading flow, section order).
- `src/sections`: page-level content sections (navigation, hero, about, skills, projects, contact, footer).
- `src/components`: reusable feature components (for example `MusicPlayer`).
- `src/components/ui`: shared UI primitives built on Radix/shadcn patterns.
- `src/context`: cross-cutting state providers (`ThemeContext`, `MusicContext`).
- `src/hooks`: custom hooks for behavior and responsive logic.
- `src/i18n`: i18n initialization and locale dictionaries.
- `src/lib`: utilities shared across components.

## Configuration Files

- `vite.config.ts`: Vite setup, React plugin, and `@` alias to `src`.
- `tailwind.config.js`: design tokens, theme extension, and Tailwind plugin setup.
- `postcss.config.js`: CSS processing pipeline.
- `eslint.config.js`: linting rules.
- `tsconfig.json`, `tsconfig.app.json`, `tsconfig.node.json`: TypeScript config split.
- `components.json`: UI component generator/config metadata.

## Navigation Guidance for Agents

- For content/layout changes, start in `src/sections` and `src/App.tsx`.
- For theming, cursor behavior, audio state, or app-level toggles, inspect `src/context`.
- For UI consistency, prefer using or extending `src/components/ui` primitives.
- For text changes, update locale files in `src/i18n/locales` rather than hardcoding.

